---
import {
  CollapsibleColumns,
  Description,
  Divider,
  ExternalLink,
  ImageWithCaption,
  InfoList,
  InfoListItem,
  PageleteSubSection,
  SubHeader,
} from "components";

import img1 from "../../imgs/product-quality-keyboard-1.svg";
import img2 from "../../imgs/product-quality-keyboard-2.svg";
import img3 from "../../imgs/product-quality-keyboard-3.svg";
import img4 from "../../imgs/product-quality-keyboard-4.svg";
import img5 from "../../imgs/product-quality-keyboard-5.svg";
---

<PageleteSubSection>
  <SubHeader id="ptg-quality-assurance-keyboard">Keyboard</SubHeader>

  <Description>
    Some users with limited mobility may navigate using only a keyboard or other
    assistive technologies, such as switch devices and voice recognition. As
    these tools emulate keyboard operations, all parts of the application need
    to be manually tested to ensure that they are reachable using a keyboard
    alone.
  </Description>

  <CollapsibleColumns>
    <ImageWithCaption
      imgSrc={img1.src}
      imgAlt="Image showing the four arrow keys on a keyboard"
      captionTitle="Ensure All Interactive Elements Can Be Reached and Triggered Using A Keyboard"
    >
      Interactive components, such as buttons, form elements, and modals, need
      to be reachable through the keyboard alone. They are activated using the
      spacebar, enter or arrow keys as appropriate. Common interaction patterns
      can be found in the documentation for each Neo component, as well as in
      the Online Resources below.
    </ImageWithCaption>

    <ImageWithCaption
      imgSrc={img2.src}
      imgAlt="Image showing a top nav with navigable links followed by a paragraph of text and then a focusable element"
      captionTitle="Use Logical Tab Order"
    >
      Users should be able to move between each item on the page in a logical
      order. Ensure the tab sequence follows a natural reading order and goes
      through each section in turn. Users must be able to navigate through all
      sections without getting stuck.
    </ImageWithCaption>
  </CollapsibleColumns>

  <CollapsibleColumns>
    <ImageWithCaption
      imgSrc={img3.src}
      imgAlt="Image showing a 'skip to main content' button"
      captionTitle="Enable Skip Navigation"
    >
      To help users easily access each section of the page, provide Quick Links
      (known as Skip Navigation) at the beginning of the tab order. However,
      landmarks must be configured first. Refer to the Online Resources for
      additional guidance.
    </ImageWithCaption>

    <ImageWithCaption
      imgSrc={img4.src}
      imgAlt="Image showing a visually focused element between two other elements"
      captionTitle="Ensure Visible Focus Style For All Interactive Elements"
    >
      Each item that receives focus should have a focus ring to provide a visual
      indication of where the user is currently on the page. All Neo components
      have a blue focus ring incorporated by default.
    </ImageWithCaption>
  </CollapsibleColumns>

  <CollapsibleColumns>
    <ImageWithCaption
      imgSrc={img5.src}
      imgAlt="Image showing a modal window with a close button being inserted into it"
      captionTitle="Ensure There Are No Keyboard Traps"
    >
      Keyboard traps occur when users get stuck in one part of an interface and
      cannot free themselves with only the keyboard. Ensure users can navigate
      through all sections without getting stuck in any area.
    </ImageWithCaption>

    <div></div>
  </CollapsibleColumns>

  <Divider />

  <CollapsibleColumns marginTop="1.5rem">
    <div>
      <b>Online Resources</b>

      <InfoList type="disc">
        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/meaningful-sequence.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 1.3.2 - Meaningful Sequence
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/keyboard.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 2.1.1- Keyboard
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/no-keyboard-trap.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 2.1.2 - No Keyboard Trap
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/bypass-blocks"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 2.4.1 - Bypassing Blocks
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/focus-order.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 2.4.3 - Focus Order
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/focus-visible.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 2.4.7 - Focus Visible
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/on-focus.html"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 3.2.1 - On Focus
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>

        <InfoListItem>
          <ExternalLink
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/consistent-navigation"
            inline={false}
          >
            WCAG Requirement 3.2.3 - Consistent Navigation
          </ExternalLink>
        </InfoListItem>
      </InfoList>
    </div>

    <div></div>
  </CollapsibleColumns>
</PageleteSubSection>
